## 3\. Core Data Models

### 3.1. The Saga Entity (Macro State)

Manages the overall lifecycle and Salesforce cursors.

```java
@Entity
@Table(name = "REVIEW_SAGA")
public class ReviewSaga {
    @Id private String reviewId;
    
    @Enumerated(EnumType.STRING)
    private SagaStep step; // HEADER, GEN_DATA, SYNC, FINALIZE, COMPLETED
    
    private String salesforceId;
    
    // Sync Cursors
    private int sfMemberOffset = 0;
    private int sfBlockOffset = 0;
    
    // Retry Management
    private int generationRetryCount = 0;
    private static final int MAX_RETRIES = 3;
}
```

### 3.2. Granular Process Status (Micro State)

**Crucial for Error Handling:** Tracks the status of *each* member independently.

```java
@Entity
@Table(name = "MEMBER_PROCESS_STATUS")
public class MemberProcessStatus {
    @Id private String id;
    
    @Column(nullable = false) private String reviewId;
    @Column(nullable = false) private String memberId;
    
    @Enumerated(EnumType.STRING)
    private ProcessStatus status; // TO_DO, PROCESSING, SUCCESS, ERROR
    
    private String errorMessage;
    private int retryCount; // Individual retry count
}
