## 5\. Resilience & Error Scenarios Matrix

| Scenario | System Behavior | Recovery Mechanism |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **API Timeout (Single Member)** | Worker catches exception, sets status `ERROR`. | Saga detects error at end of batch, increments retry count, and re-dispatches ONLY this member. |
| **Container Crash (During Gen)** | In-memory threads die. DB rows stay `PROCESSING` or `TO_DO`. | On restart, a Scheduled Task detects "stuck" `PROCESSING` rows \> 10min and resets them to `TO_DO`. |
| **Salesforce Limit Reached** | Sync Loop fails one batch. | Saga cursor is NOT updated. Next retry resumes at the exact same batch. No data loss. |
| **Event Registry Limit** | N/A | Prevented by using **Pull Pattern** (IDs fetched via Interface, not Event). |

